# Parallel Rotation Engine
# Phase 7 & Phase 8 Stability Rules

Status: LOCKED AFTER VERIFICATION

These rules protect the Phase 7 and Phase 8 behavior of the rotation engine.
All changes must preserve the verified scheduling behavior and fairness metrics.

---

## 1. Core Behavior (DO NOT CHANGE)

The following pipeline has been verified and must remain intact:

STRICT search
    ↓
If no valid plan exists
    ↓
BEAM_EXHAUSTED
    ↓
Fallback to RELAXED mode
    ↓
Generate viable rotation plan
    ↓
Return explain data + fairness metrics

The engine must always produce a schedule when hard constraints allow it.

---

## 2. Rotation Explain Layer (Phase 7)

The explain system must continue to expose:

- weeks[]
- hardValidCandidatesCount
- totalCandidatesCount
- rejectedBy
- failureReason
- rotationForced
- weekHasMultipleBestCandidates

This data is used for debugging, algorithm verification, and UI transparency.

Do not remove or rename these fields.

Explain output must remain deterministic for identical inputs.

---

## 3. Relaxed Mode Behavior (Phase 8)

When STRICT mode cannot produce a shareable plan:

shareablePlanExists = false  
forcedReason = "BEAM_EXHAUSTED"  
modeUsed = "RELAXED"

The engine must still return a valid rotation schedule.

This fallback is **intentional and correct behavior**.

Do not treat this as an error.

---

## 4. Fairness Metrics

The algorithm must continue returning the following metrics:

currentPlanMetrics:
    maxBurden
    minBurden
    spread
    maxBurdenMemberIds
    consecutiveMax
    sumPenalty

These metrics are used for:

- fairness validation
- UI fairness summary
- rotation transparency

Do not change metric semantics without a full regression test.

---

## 5. Rotation Forcing

The engine may mark:

rotationForced: true

when the best candidate exceeds fairness constraints but is still selected.

This is expected behavior for extreme timezone distributions.

Do not remove this flag.

---

## 6. Determinism Requirement

For identical inputs the engine must produce identical outputs.

Given the same:

team members  
timezones  
constraints  
weeks  
base time  

the generated rotation must be deterministic.

If randomness is introduced it must be seeded.

---

## 7. Protected Components

The following components must remain stable:

lib/rotation.ts
generateRotation()
generateRotationGuarded()
beam search candidate scoring
fairness scoring logic
rotation penalty evaluation

Changes to these areas require explicit regression testing.

---

## 8. UI Contract

The rotation UI relies on the following fields:

modeUsed  
shareablePlanExists  
forcedReason  
weeks[]  
currentPlanMetrics  

These fields must remain backward compatible.

Do not rename them without updating the UI.

---

## 9. Change Control

Do NOT:

- refactor fairness scoring
- change penalty weights
- alter beam search depth
- modify candidate filtering

unless a full regression test pack is executed.

---

## 10. Testing Requirement

Any modification to the rotation engine must pass:

Phase 0 — Determinism  
Phase 1 — Input Contract  
Phase 2 — Hard Constraints  
Phase 3 — Fairness Logic  
Phase 4 — Boundary Guards  
Phase 5 — Explain Layer  
Phase 6 — Strict / Relaxed Fallback  
Phase 7 — Explain Validation  
Phase 8 — Fairness Metrics Validation

Status: VERIFIED

These rules extend the rotation engine protection after completing
Phase 7, Phase 8, Pack I and Pack J verification.

The goal is to guarantee algorithm stability, performance boundaries,
and correct fallback behavior.

---

# 1. Verified Solver Pipeline

The rotation engine pipeline is now verified and must remain intact.

STRICT search
↓
If no shareable plan exists
↓
BEAM_EXHAUSTED
↓
Fallback to RELAXED
↓
If still infeasible
↓
FALLBACK mode
↓
Return best available plan + explain metrics

The solver must **never silently fail**.

---

# 2. Mode Semantics (DO NOT CHANGE)

The engine can return three modes:

STRICT  
RELAXED  
FALLBACK

Rules:

STRICT  
A fairness-valid plan exists.

RELAXED  
Fairness constraints were softened.

FALLBACK  
Beam search exhausted without producing a fairness-valid schedule.

The solver must **honestly report which mode was used**.

---

# 3. Explain Contract

The explain system must continue exposing:

weeks[]
hardValidCandidatesCount
totalCandidatesCount
rejectedBy
failureReason
rotationForced
weekHasMultipleBestCandidates

These fields support algorithm transparency and debugging.

Do not rename or remove them.

---

# 4. Fairness Metrics Contract

The engine must return:

currentPlanMetrics
bestPlanMetrics

Metrics include:

maxBurden  
minBurden  
spread  
maxBurdenMemberIds  
consecutiveMax  
sumPenalty

These metrics power UI summaries and fairness evaluation.

Do not change metric semantics without regression tests.

---

# 5. Pack I Verification (20 Member Load Test)

Pack I verified the solver remains stable with:

• 20 participants  
• global timezone distribution  
• 8-week rotation

Observed behavior:

modeUsed = FALLBACK  
shareablePlanExists = false  
forcedReason = BEAM_EXHAUSTED

Generation time remained ~2–3 seconds.

This establishes the **current performance envelope**.

The solver must remain stable at this scale.

---

# 6. Pack J Verification (Candidate Density Test)

Pack J verified stability when candidate density increases.

Configuration:

• wide working hours (7–21)
• 12 members
• multi-timezone
• no hard boundaries

Observed behavior:

hardValidCandidatesCount ≈ 48 per week
modeUsed = FALLBACK
forcedReason = BEAM_EXHAUSTED

No solver instability or performance degradation occurred.

---

# 7. Beam Search Guard

The beam width parameter:

FAIRNESS_BEAM_WIDTH

Current verified value:

200

This parameter controls search breadth.

Changes must be validated with Pack I and Pack J.

Do not reduce beam width without testing.

---

# 8. Determinism Requirement

The solver must be deterministic.

For identical inputs:

team members  
timezones  
constraints  
meeting cadence  
weeks  

The output rotation must remain identical.

No randomness may affect scheduling.

---

# 9. Protected Components

The following components are protected:

lib/rotation.ts
generateRotation()
generateRotationGuarded()
beam search scoring
fairness scoring
candidate enumeration

Changes require full regression testing.

---

# 10. Change Control

Do NOT modify:

fairness scoring weights  
beam width defaults  
candidate enumeration logic  
fallback pipeline

Unless all rotation test packs pass again.

---

